Airport Coordinates

Rodrigo Suzuki Okada

2/13/2017

Dataset

This web presentation features a map of airports around the world, created with Leaflet in R.

The dataset itself is available here. It consists of a list of airports by ICAO code, latitude, longitude and altitude (in feet).

airports <- read.csv("icao_airports.csv", 
                     col.names = c("code", "lat", "lng", "alt"))
head(airports)
##   code      lat        lng     alt
## 1 00AZ 34.30559 -112.16460 3810.04
## 2  00B 38.91472  -76.50472    0.00
## 3  00C 37.20318 -107.86919 6684.06
## 4 00CA 35.35053 -116.88837 3038.06
## 5 00CL 38.63824 -121.51523   21.98
## 6 00CO 40.62220 -104.34440 4830.05

Preparing the map

Each marker on the map will be presented with a airplane icon. The original file is available on Wikimedia Commons.

airplaneIcon <- makeIcon(iconUrl = "airplane_icon.png", 
                         iconWidth = 32, iconHeight = 32, 
                         iconAnchorX = 16, iconAnchorY = 16)

The markers will have popup information with the airports code and coordinates.

airports$legend <- paste(airports$code, 
                         paste("lat", airports$lat, sep = " "), 
                         paste("lng", airports$lng, sep = " "), 
                         sep = "<br/>")
